## 2026-02-22 — Component decomposition

### What changed

All large page components were split into small sub-components placed in `ui/` subdirectories:

- `home.svelte` (380→115 lines): `MediaCard`, `MediaFilterBar`, `AddMediaModal`
- `media-details.svelte` (407→117 lines): `MediaHero`, `MediaProgressPanel`
- `profile.svelte` (404→134 lines): `ProfileInfo`, `ProviderApiKeyRow`, `DeleteAccountModal`
- `list-details.svelte` (144→49 lines): `ListDetailHeader` + reuses `MediaCard`
- `lists.svelte` (120→72 lines): `CreateListForm`

### Why

- Page root components are now thin composers (< 120 lines), all logic/UI in `ui/` sub-components
- `MediaCard` is shared between home grid and list-details grid; accepts `showStatusLabel?: boolean` to toggle status label vs. icon-only mode; also accepts `currentSeason?` / `currentEpisode?` for progress display in hover overlay

### Rule

Page roots must remain thin composers. New features go in `ui/` sub-components, not in the page root.

