## 2026-02-23 — Kanban board (`/board`)

### What was built
- New page `src/routes/board/+page.svelte` + `+page.server.ts`
- FSD slice: `src/pages/board/` with `board.svelte`, `board.types.ts`, `index.ts`
- Sub-components: `ui/kanban-column.svelte`, `ui/kanban-card.svelte`, `ui/episodic-watched-dialog.svelte`
- Sidebar link added to `app-sidebar.svelte`
- i18n keys added to all 5 locale files (`board_*` prefix)

### Architecture decisions

**dndzone must have direct DOM children**
`svelte-dnd-action` drags ALL direct children of the dndzone element. Any wrapping `<div>` inside makes the library treat the wrapper as the single draggable unit (all cards fly together). Fix: use `flex flex-col gap-2` on the dndzone itself, no inner wrappers.

**Each column owns local drag state**
`KanbanColumn` manages `let localItems = $state(untrack(() => [...items]))`. The dndzone works against `localItems`, never against the prop. A `$effect` syncs from prop when `!isDragging`.
```svelte
$effect(() => {
  const incoming = items   // always read to track as dependency
  if (!isDragging) localItems = [...incoming]
})
```

**Cross-column status change detection**
Use `TRIGGERS.DROPPED_INTO_ZONE` from `svelte-dnd-action` + check original item status:
```typescript
import { TRIGGERS } from 'svelte-dnd-action'
if (trigger === TRIGGERS.DROPPED_INTO_ZONE) {
  const movedItem = event_.detail.items.find(i => String(i.id) === movedId)
  const crossColumn = movedItem && (movedItem.status ?? 'PLAN_TO_WATCH') !== status
  if (crossColumn) await onStatusChange(movedId, status)
}
```

**`onStatusChange` returns `Promise<void>`**
The column `await`s it — `isDragging` stays `true` during PATCH + `refetchQueries`, preventing `$effect` from syncing with stale data. After the promise resolves `isDragging = false` and `$effect` syncs with fresh server data.

**Episodic → Watched dialog**
When episodic media (TV/ANIME) is dropped into Watched, board.svelte stores a `resolve` function:
```typescript
type PendingMove = { itemId: string; item: KanbanItem; resolve: () => void }
// handleStatusChange returns new Promise<void>(resolve => { pendingMove = { ..., resolve } })
// handleDialogConfirm/Cancel calls resolve() after PATCH + refetchQueries
```

**FLIP animation**
`animate:flip` must be on a DOM element, not a component. Wrap each `{#each}` item:
```svelte
{#each localItems as item (item.id)}
  <div animate:flip={{ duration: flipDurationMs }}>
    ...card or shadow...
  </div>
{/each}
```
Pass matching `flipDurationMs` to `use:dndzone={{ ..., flipDurationMs }}`.

**Shadow item rendering**
Shadow items (drop-position indicator) are rendered as the actual card at `opacity-40 pointer-events-none`:
```svelte
{#if (item as Record<string, unknown>)[SHADOW_ITEM_MARKER_PROPERTY_NAME]}
  <div class="pointer-events-none select-none opacity-40">
    <KanbanCard {item} />
  </div>
{:else}
  <KanbanCard {item} />
{/if}
```

**Ghost cards (IN_PROGRESS shown in Watched)**
Episodic IN_PROGRESS items with episode progress appear at the **top** of the Watched column (above the dndzone) as `<KanbanCard ghost />`. They are `$derived` from `allItems` in `board.svelte`.

**Optimistic status update on drop**
When cross-column drop detected, immediately update the moved item's `status` in `localItems` before awaiting the server:
```typescript
localItems = event_.detail.items.map(item =>
  String(item.id) === movedId ? { ...item, status } : item
)
```

**`refetchQueries` vs `invalidateQueries`**
Board uses `queryClient.refetchQueries(...)` (waits for refetch to complete) rather than `invalidateQueries` (fire-and-forget). This ensures `items` prop is fresh when `isDragging` resets.

